Label: Seasonal Adjustment
Comment: Whether the time-series has been adjusted to remove cyclical components

Label: Age of Business
Comment: How long the business has been trading

Label: Trade Partner Geography
Comment: Location of the trade partner. Typically a foreign geography. The destination of exports or origin of imports.

Label: Trade Reporter Geography
Comment: Location of the trade reporter. Typically a domestic geography. The destination of imports or origin of exports.

Label: International Trade Basis
Comment: The methodological basis on which the trade statistics have been calculated

Label: Investment Direction
Comment: Direction of foreign direct investment into the UK (inward) or abroad (outward)

Label: Export and Import Activity
Comment: Whether and how the business is trading internationally

Label: ONS FDI Area
Comment: Area from which foreign direct investment (FDI) flows into/out of the UK

Label: FDI Component
Comment: Foreign direct investment (FDI) component being measured

Label: FDI Industry
Comment: High level industry groupings based on SIC 2007

Label: NUTS Geography
Comment: The Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics (NUTS) is a geocode standard by Eurostat for referencing the subdivisions of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland for statistical purposes.

Label: ONS Functional Category
Comment: ONS high level industry groupings based on SIC 2007

Label: Standard Industrial Classification
Comment: The current Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) used in classifying business establishments and other statistical units by the type of economic activity in which they are engaged.

Label: Size of Business by Number of Employees
Comment: Size of a business based on the number of employees

Label: HMRC Reporter Region
Comment: Location of the trade reporter Typically a domestic geography The destination of imports or origin of exports

Label: Flow
Comment: Direction in which trade is measured
